info, upload reports, and connect devices to participate actively in care."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can patients add health data from wearables or mobile health apps?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The EHR supports 70+ trackers and integrates with Google Health Connect, Apple Health, and connected devices to share real-time vitals, symptoms, and test results."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do providers use the EHR during virtual consultations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can upload lab reports and device data before visits. During sessions, providers see a snapshot of the profile and recent data, then log notes, prescribe, order labs, and assign monitoring plans—all linked to the record."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the EHR customizable for different specialties or practices?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Practices choose which of the 70+ trackers to enable, configure profile sections, and control Health Journal visibility to match their clinical focus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are medical reports and imaging handled?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The system stores PDFs, scans, and DICOM imaging with role-based access. Both patients and providers can upload reports, which are searchable and available for secure download."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the EHR ensure data privacy and compliance?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Security includes role-based permissions, audit trails, and encryption. Patients control sharing, all access is logged, and PHI/PII is never sent over insecure channels like SMS or email."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can providers collaborate with patients through the Health Journal?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Patients add journal entries and providers can comment, creating a two-way conversation that improves engagement and decision-making."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the EHR only for virtual care, or does it support in-clinic workflows too?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It supports both. The same EHR powers in-person visits, video consultations, and remote monitoring to maintain continuity across care settings."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What practices or healthcare businesses benefit most from this EHR?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Small practices, clinics, and healthcare startups that need an all-in-one system with integrated services, patient engagement, and scalable digital health capabilities."}}]}</script><section class="py-16 bg-gray-50"><div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><div class="text-center mb-12"><h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="w-24 h-1 bg-blue-vibrant mx-auto"></div></div><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8"><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="What makes the Virtual Practice EHR different from other EHR systems?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">What makes the Virtual Practice EHR different from other EHR systems?</span><span class="transform transition-transform ">▼</span></button></div><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="How does the EHR support both providers and patients?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">How does the EHR support both providers and patients?</span><span class="transform transition-transform ">▼</span></button></div><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="Can patients add health data from wearables or mobile health apps?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">Can patients add health data from